The evidence with the title 'Economic policy of the George W. Bush administration - Wikipedia ' says Measured for fiscal years 2001-2008, federal spending under president Bush averaged 19.0 % of gdp, just below his predecessor president Bill Clinton at 19.2 % gdp, although tax receipts were substantially lower at 17.1% gdp versus 18.4 % gdp. Income tax revenues averaged 7.7% gdp under Bush, versus 8.5% gdp  ... 
